South Africa wrap up the home summer of cricket against Bangladesh. eNCA's Hloni Mtimkulu reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa play host to Bangladesh for the next month. First up is the ODI series, before switching over to the long format. Despite the Tigers offering a different kind of intensity compared to the likes of India, captain Temba Bavuma has stressed there will be no complacency against the visitors. All three ODIs will be played on the Highveld, with Bavuma confident his side can take advantage of the familiar conditions offered by the Wanderers and SuperSport Park wickets. * eNCA's Hloni Mtimkulu reports.